PORT = 5000
GITHUB_TOKEN = your_github_token

Steps:
1. Go to the Token Settings Page
Choose “Fine-grained personal access tokens”

2. Click “Generate new token”   

3. Configure Access
Token name: Give a clear name - e.g. profile-readme-access

Expiration: Set as needed (e.g. 90 days)

Resource Owner: Select your GitHub username (your own account).

Repository Access: Choose All repositories if you want to access both public and private repos.

Repository permissions
a. Contents → Read-only
b. Metadata → Read-only

4. Generate Token
Click “Generate token”.
Copy the token immediately — you won’t see it again!